Forwarded from: Ministry of Agriculture of Kherson region
❗️Free economic zone in new regions of the Russian Federation The Ministry of Agriculture of the Kherson region draws attention to the fact that in order to ensure sustainable socio-economic development of new constituent entities of the Russian Federation, on behalf of the President and Government of the Russian Federation, from July 1, 2023, a free economic zone (FEZ) was created on the territory of new constituent entities of the Russian Federation in accordance with the Federal Law from June 24, 2023 No. 266-FZ “On the free economic zone in the territories of the Donetsk People's Republic, Lugansk People's Republic, Zaporozhye region and Kherson region.” A special regime for entrepreneurial and other activities operates on the territory of the FEZ, which provides for:✓tax benefits and preferences;
✓free customs zone;
✓preferential procedure for providing land plots for rent;
✓simplification of approval procedures in urban planning activities;
✓preferential lending. Conditions for entry into the SEZ: Registration in the new region of a legal entity (branch) or individual entrepreneur. The volume of capital investments for the first three years of activity in the SEZ territory is not less than:✓1 million rubles - for IT projects, scientific research and development;✓ 3 million rubles - for small and medium-sized businesses; ✓30 million rubles - for other persons. The volume of capital investments in the first year of implementation of the investment project is at least 30% of the total volume of capital investments, if the implementation of the project is not related to the need for design, construction or reconstruction capital construction projects. SEZ management bodies: Ministry of Construction of Russia and management company - PPK "Territory Development Fund". Full information can be found on the website of the Territory Development Fund. Registration here. #Ministry of Agriculture_Kherson_region@APKKherson

